 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search Facilities Manager iRhythm Technologies 55 reviews San Francisco, CA 94103 iRhythm Technologies 55 reviews Read what people are saying about working here. Job Company Job details Job Type Full-time Full Job Description About iRhythm: 
iRhythm is a leading digital healthcare company focused on the way cardiac arrhythmias are clinically diagnosed by combining our wearable bio sensing technology with powerful cloud-based data analytics and Artificial Intelligence capabilities. Our goal is to be the leading provider of ambulatory ECG monitoring for patients at risk for arrhythmias. iRhythm's continuous ambulatory monitoring has already put over 2 million patients and their doctors on a shorter path to what they both need â€“ answers.
 
 About this role: 
iRhythm is currently seeking an experienced, motivated Facilities Manager to be based out of our San Francisco or Lincolnshire, IL Offices. The mission of this role is to ensure a positive and safe workplace experience every day for these locations. This means striking a fine balance between the optimal and the exceptional in the way our workspace is organized and used. This individual will overcome the "behind the scenes" challenges ensuring a seamless process for our employees and visitors. Our work environment is fast-paced, with a collaborative atmosphere. Most of all, we are passionate about delivering innovations that improve the quality of health care and the patient experience.
 
 Specific job responsibilities: 
Lead office management teams in San Francisco and other iRhythm locations.
 
Ensure that our office environments are comfortable, effective, and productive as possible, meeting the needs of our internal customers and employees
 
Deliver innovative workplace hospitality services and operations for the iRhythm offices, including meeting & event services, partnering with event planning, food service, mailroom, A.V. support, custodial, corporate reception, shipping, receiving and supplies management
 
Establish effective processes to monitor, inspect, and maintain all buildings and equipment to ensure efficient operation of utility systems (mechanical, electrical, structural, and plumbing, etc.)
 
Serve as liaison to senior management and regulatory agencies, (i.e. OSHA) on all facility matters
 
Champion day-to-day building operations to ensure service reliability and work environment standards are achieved, including participating in buildouts, relocations, decommissioning, furniture solutions, and maintenance activities
 
Take direct ownership of office operations to ensure a first-class office experience, including preparation for new hires, safety and security, food and beverage services, and janitorial services
 
Partner with the building management and landlords coordinating cleaning and maintenance services
 
Maintain effective relationships with vendors to ensure that quality pricing and work is complete on time and budget.
 
Ensure compliance with legal requirements, building rules and applicable ordinances
 
Assist management in development and reporting of EHS performance metrics to facilitate continuous, ongoing improvement of the EHS efforts and results
 
Develop strong working relationships with Cypress Facilities and EHS Manager to ensure consistent services and programs
 
Manage collection of key performance indicator metrics and perform analysis to support workplace strategy and practical process improvement
 
Conduct routine, scheduled facility inspections and audits to monitor and detect potential safety, health, and environmental hazards. Ensure PPE compliance among employees recommend corrective action or preventative measures where indicated and appropriate. Process reports, documents findings and actions taken.
 
Ensure the company remains compliant with all OSHA, COVID-19 requirements and other safety related regulations as well as insurance carrier requirements
 
Assist with RTO (return to office) workplace efforts in San Francisco, Houston and Lincolnshire
 
 About you: 
You are an experienced Facilities Management professional with 10+ years' experience in leading a workplace team, facilities management, construction and building operations. The ideal candidate will leverage their critical thinking and influencing skills to plan and execute projects meaningfully, while improving the facility and employee experience. You must be able to work in a collaborative, fast-moving, and ambiguous environment while being an effective communicator and influence cross-functional teams.
 
Bachelor's Degree in Facilities Management, Environmental Science, Environmental Sustainability OR equivalent work experience preferred .
 
Solid knowledge of property and facility management, leases / contract review and construction terms and practices
 
Broad purchasing and contracting experience
 
Expertise in the creation, negotiation, and administration of contracts
 
Ability to oversee and implement strong internal processes that drive effectiveness across organization
 
Ability to lead and manage a team and key stakeholder relationships
 
Strong communication skills with the ability to communicate effectively at any level and present financial and contract recommendations
 
Exceptional organizational and analytical skills, and a proven ability to drive complex projects with aggressive schedules with minimal oversight
 
Knowledge of OSHA rules, regulations and compliance concerning the workplace
 
Certified Safety Professional â€“ CSP and/or OSHA Certifications required.
 
Flexibility to respond and react to any facility emergencies on a 24/7 basis, along with having flexible with work hours to support all operations and shifts
 
The ability to travel 25%
 
What's in it for you?
 
This is a full-time position with a competitive compensation package, excellent benefits including medical, dental and vision insurance (all of which start on your first day), paid holidays, and PTO!
 
iRhythm also provides additional benefits including 401K (with company match), an Employee Stock Purchase Plan, paid parental leave, pet insurance discount, Cultural Committee/Charity events, and so much more!
 
 FLSA Status :  Exempt
 
As a part of our core values, we ensure a diverse and inclusive workforce. We welcome and celebrate people of all backgrounds, experiences, skills and perspectives. iRhythm Technologies, Inc. is an Equal Opportunity Employer (M/F/V/D). Pursuant to San Francisco Fair Chance Ordinance, we will consider for employment all qualified applicants with arrest and conviction records.
 
